<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Phrase 1 (mm. 1-8): Open quartal/open-5th voicings (I: G2-D3-G3, V: D2-A2-D3).
  RH 2-note open 4th/5th pairs. Mirrors the open, joyful character of the opening.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 9-15): Fuller 3-note triads emerge. LH adds 3rd (B2 in G chord)
  for richer sound. RH follows melodic contour with stepwise inner-voice motion.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 16-21): Full 4-note LH voicings (G2-B2-D3-G3), V7 chords (D2-A2-C3),
  suspensions. Climactic measures use full triad + octave doublings.
- Final cadence: Root-position I with full 4+3 voice layout. Pedal G2 anchors.
- Non-diatonic substitutions: Am→②m, A7→⑤7, A major→⑤ (nearest diatonic).

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Inner alto voice (RH top note) follows melodic contour in thirds below melody.
- LH bass moves by 4th/5th only; no 2nds in bass register (P4/P5 rule maintained).
- Measures 6-7: contrary motion between soprano (descending G-F#-E) and bass (D-D-G ascending).
- Measure 18: chromatic-feeling D7 → G descent matches the lyric descent of the melody.
- Suspensions at phrase ends (m. 20): V chord delays resolution to I.

TEXTURE ARC:
- mm. 1-4: 2-note hands, open spacing, quartal flavor — fresh and clear
- mm. 5-9: 3-note LH, gentle 2-note RH — builds warmth
- mm. 10-15: Full triads in LH, passing notes in RH — middle density
- mm. 16-20: 4-note LH, 3-note RH — full harp texture, climactic arrival
- m. 21: Root-position convergence, sustained — final repose
-->
